HEADWORD: manul
<hw>ma"nul</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A wild cat (<spn>Felis manul</spn>), having long, soft,
light-colored fur. It is found in the mountains of Central Asia, and
dwells among rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

